article.headline: Dartmouth 88, Daniel Webster 52
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- DeVon Mosley scored 18 points and grabbed nine rebounds as Dartmouth ended its 12-day exam break with an 88-52 victory over Daniel Webster on Saturday night. Mosley made 4-of-6 shots from beyond the arc to help the Big Green (5-4) win for the fourth time in their last five games. Alex Barnett added 10 points and six assists for Dartmouth and Adam Powers had 12 points in 11 minutes. Daniel Webster (3-4), playing its first official game ever against a Division I opponent, got 17 points from Brian Inge and nine from Ahmad Hemingway. The Eagles were held to 31.9 percent shooting. Dartmouth jumped to a 44-19 halftime lead and added to it with 57.1 percent shooting from the field in the second half. The Big Green finished with season-highs of 26 assists, 12 blocks and 50 percent shooting from 3-point range (8-for-16). Ten players scored for Dartmouth, which got 26 points off its bench and never trailed.
